{{see|Manual}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[manualis|manuālis]]''', adjectival form of '''[[manus]]''' ''hand'', and derived term '''[[manuale|manuāle]]''' ''handbook'', ''manual''.

===Pronunciation===
* [[GenAm]] {{IPA|/ˈmænjuəl/}}, {{SAMPA|/"m{nju@l/}}

*'''Hyphenation:''' man·u·al

====Homophones====
*[[Manuel]] ''(anglicized pronunciation)''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A booklet that instructs on the usage of a particular machine.
# {{music}} A [[keyboard]] for the hands on a [[harpsichord]], [[organ]], or other multiple-keyboard instrument (as opposed to a '''[[pedal]]''', which is a keyboard for the feet.)
# A manual [[transmission]]; a [[gearbox]], especially of a motorized vehicle, shifted by the operator.
# {{italbrac|by syndoche}} A vehicle with a manual transmission.

